    show sc w2trishahousemow m04
    c"Well, [s_name] and [y_name] want me to help them with the hotel, and to specifically run the front desk area."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m02
    c"But I don‚Äôt know if I can do it. It seems like a huge amount of responsibility."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m09
    tri"Really? How did this come about?"
    show sc w2trishahousemow m05
    c"It all started when [s_name] told [y_name] that I owned half the hotel..."
    c"And that I‚Äôd also been studying that hotel management course you recommended that I take."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m04
    c"So now they think that it would be good for me to work alongside them both while I‚Äôm still studying."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"You know what? I think they‚Äôre right."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m05
    c"You do?"
    show sc w2trishahousemow m12
    tri"Yes, of course. There‚Äôs nothing wrong with working as a receptionist or in an office sweetheart."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"That‚Äôs basically what I‚Äôve been doing for the past ten or so years."
    tri"And it‚Äôs also a good chance for you to work on your social anxiety issues."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m11
    tri"Heaven knows I‚Äôve tried to help you with that..."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m09
    tri"But I think your cousin [s_name] and this guy [y_name] might be able to help more than I ever could."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m03
    c"Okay, but what if I fail at this? What if I royally stuff things up for [s_name]? It‚Äôs so much pressure."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"You‚Äôll never know until you try [c_name]."
    tri"And besides, you need to start putting yourself out there and the hotel I believe is the best place to start. You can do this, I know you can."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m09
    tri"I mean you sounded like you were very comfortable being around [y_name], correct?"
    show sc w2trishahousemow m06
    c"Yeah, he‚Äôs really easy to talk to. I like his company and he‚Äôs helped me out in so many ways already."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"Well there you go. Look, just try your best sweetheart. That‚Äôs all I ask of you."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m07
    c"Okay Mom, I will."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"How about you call your cousin [s_name] and see if she needs any help over there this morning?"
    tri"I‚Äôm sure she‚Äôd appreciate it."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m06
    c"Okay, I‚Äôll call her after I‚Äôve finished breakfast. Thanks Mom."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m12
    tri"You‚Äôre welcome honey."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"And if you‚Äôre going to be working behind the front desk of a beachside hotel, it‚Äôs best that you try and look the part."
    tri"First appearances in such establishments are a huge deal, and guests who are looking to stay there will be seeing you first."
    show sc w2trishahousemow m09
    tri"Do you understand what I‚Äôm saying?"
    show sc w2trishahousemow m05
    c"Yeah, I do Mom."
    c"(Hmm‚Ä¶ What on earth am I going to wear??)"
    show sc w2trishahousemow m08
    tri"(That should get her out of the house for a few hours. At some point I should drop into the hotel myself.)"
    tri"(It would be the ideal chance for me to follow up on my last conversation with [y_name], which I‚Äôm sure will be very interesting, to say the least‚Ä¶)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)












label lb_w2_cup_final:
    # Day 4 (MOW) 16 - MC listens to the cup final on his radio"
    # *NOTE: MD - Try and make the room that the MC is painting, NOT a hotel room, because it‚Äôs mentioned in the first half of this update that all the rooms in the east wing have now been painted by this point. The west wing is still closed."
    # So maybe have him painting the lobby area or the health centre room perhaps?"
    # SCENE BEGINS"
    # (scene begins with the MC listening to the radio in a half-painted room)"
    scene sc w2_mow_paintingroom p01
    with dissolve
    mc"(Come on, see these last few seconds out‚Ä¶ Don‚Äôt fucking throw it away now!)"
    mc"(Man‚Ä¶ This shitty season might actually have a satisfying ending.)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p02
    rad"THAT‚ÄôS IT! IT‚ÄôS ALL OVER! THEY‚ÄôVE WON THE CUP FOR A RECORD FOURTEENTH TIME!"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p03
    mc"YESS! GET IN THERE!"
    # (MC pumps his fist)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p05
    mc"(Hopefully now our stingy-arse board gives Auba whatever he wants after that performance!)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p06
    mc"(But they‚Äôll probably find a way to still fuck things up‚Ä¶)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p04
    mc"(I can only imagine what my ex-boss is thinking right now. He must be devastated.)"
    mc"(Good‚Ä¶)"
    # (Friend enters the room)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p12
    s"Hey, what‚Äôs going on [y_name]? I thought I heard some yelling."
    # (MC runs over to friend and hugs her, lifts her up off the ground)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p17
    with vpunch
    mc"They did it! They won!! "
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc w2_mow_paintingroom p17","sc w2_mow_paintingroom p17x","v_pt_image_index_w2_25")
    s"Whoah! Someone‚Äôs excited!"
    s"What on earth are you talking about [y_name]?"
    mc"My team. That actually won the cup final. I was just listening to it on the radio."
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p14
    s"Cup final? Oh, you mean some version of football, right?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p09
    mc"Yeah! It‚Äôs been our worst season in nearly twenty-five years and somehow they still managed to win something."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p12
    s"Well I‚Äôm really happy for you [y_name], but, have you done any actual work in here during the past hour?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p18
    s"This room should‚Äôve been finished by now!"
    # (show a shot of the half-painted room)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p12
    mc"Oh, right. Yeah, sorry about that [s_name]."
    s"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p15
    s"It‚Äôs fine, but we really need to get this room finished as quickly as possible."
    s"So I‚Äôm going to have to help you to do that now."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p09
    mc"(Ahh shit. I can tell she‚Äôs not happy with me. I couldn‚Äôt concentrate as soon as we went in front.)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p20
    s"I‚Äôll never understand why guys are so passionate about watching or hearing about other guys kicking or throwing a ball around."
    mc"Haha, what can I say?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p19
    mc"Once I was hooked into this game then was no turning back, even despite how crappy my team has been for most of this season."
    mc"(And several seasons before this one.)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p19
    s"Anyway, let‚Äôs get back to work."
    s"My cousin [c_name] is coming over very soon and I don‚Äôt want us to still be painting when she arrives."
    mc"[c_name]‚Äôs coming here?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    s"Yeah, she called me about ten minutes ago, and said that she was interested in learning more about the business."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p22
    s"Isn‚Äôt that great?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    mc"Oh yeah, that‚Äôs awesome. Are you going to show her the front desk that she might be working in?"
    # (friend picks up a brush and starts painting a wall that needs new paint)"
    s"That‚Äôs one of things I‚Äôd like to show her, yeah."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p19
    s"However, what I had in mind was for both you and me to work together with her..."
    s"And to try and teach her the ins and outs of working behind the front desk."
    s"We also need to assess how she handles various situations."
    s"What do you think?"
    mc"Oh, so some of it will be kind of like role-playing then?"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    s"Yeah, exactly."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p19
    s"I‚Äôve had some troublesome guests in the past so it would be interesting to use those scenarios on [c_name], and to teach her how to best handle each situation."
    s"She needs to be able to do this if she wants to run the front desk you see."
    s"So, what do you think?"
    mc"I think it‚Äôs a great idea, and I feel like she‚Äôll be up to the task."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    s"I have a few other things that we can go through with [c_name], like showing her where everything is in the main office and at the front desk."
    s"But we can go through all that once she arrives."
    s"We‚Äôll also need to teach [c_name] how to take bookings, to show her the emails that she will need to forward through to me, answering phone calls, that kind of thing."
    s"And anything else you can think of. I‚Äôd like her to be able to handle everything by the end of the week if possible."
    mc"No problems, we‚Äôll get her up to scratch I‚Äôm sure."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p19
    mc"So, did you have any plans for after we‚Äôre done with [c_name]?"
    s"Well I need to head to the mall actually."
    s"The reason being is that Jazmin has given me a list of things that she‚Äôs recommended that I get for the health centre, and I‚Äôd like to do that today."
    mc"Okay, sounds good."
    mc"I‚Äôll keep chipping away here while you‚Äôre gone, and try to finish any of the odd jobs that still need to be completed around the hotel."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p22
    s"Great. All right, we better get to work."
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    s"And by the way, you owe me one [y_name], for helping you to finish this room."
    # (friend winks at him)"
    mc"Fair enough [s_name]. I promise I‚Äôll make it up to you. I‚Äôm in such a good mood right now!"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p22
    s"Boy, if you‚Äôre this happy when your team wins, I‚Äôd hate to see what you‚Äôre like when they lose!"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p21
    mc"Oh, I can assure you that you don‚Äôt ever want to see that!"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p22
    s"Hahaha!"
    # (MC goes back to painting, focuses on the wall, friend paints alongside him as he thinks)"
    show sc w2_mow_paintingroom p23
    mc"(Hmm‚Ä¶ Why is it that adults aren't supposed to go mad about anything, especially when it comes to sport? You‚Äôre expected to keep a lid on it.)"
    mc"(And if you don't then people are apparently entitled to say whatever they like.)"
    mc"(‚ÄúYou haven't grown up. You're a moron. Your conversation is trivial and boorish. You can't express your emotional needs. You can't relate to your children.‚Äù)"
    mc"(However, for the first time in a long while, I‚Äôm starting to believe that the team‚Äôs current mood and fortunes somehow are reflecting my own.)"
    mc"(I‚Äôm in a good place right now, unlike a few weeks ago when I was always stressed out and nothing was going right, much like the team I support.)"
    mc"(I guess all sports fans go through this kind of thing, which I suppose makes me exactly like everybody else.)"
    mc"(I better do some work. At least I don‚Äôt have to think about football for the next few weeks at least‚Ä¶)"
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)






label lb_w2_c_frontdesk_job:
    # Day 4 (MOW) 17 - Cousin arrives at the hotel to learn more about the front desk job"
    # SCENE BEGINS"
    # (scene begins with the MC and friend finishing up the room)"
    scene sc w2cfrontdesk f08
    with dissolve
    s"There, that should just about do it."
    mc"It came up pretty good, didn‚Äôt it?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f06
    s"Yeah, it looks better than ever! The colour we chose makes the room look like it‚Äôs brand-new."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f01
    c"Hey guys!"
    # (Friend and the MC turn around, and see that cousin has arrived, wearing a receptionist or business type outfit)"
    # ROLLING WIP OF COUSIN"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f10
    mc"Hi [c_name]."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f03
    s"Hey [c_name], right on time!"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f04
    s"Wait, what is that you‚Äôre wearing?!"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f14
    c"Oh, well, after we spoke on the phone, I figured that I should try and dress the part, especially if I‚Äôm going to be doing some work in the office."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f05
    c"It‚Äôs not too much, is it?"
    # (Cousin changes pose in her outfit here)"
    # [Yeah it is / You look great]"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f09
    menu:
        "Yeah it is":
            mc"It probably is, because what we will be doing with your this morning is only meant to be a relaxing session in the front reception area where we‚Äôll mainly be working."
            mc"But not to worry, it shouldn‚Äôt matter too much."
            mc"I‚Äôm sure [s_name] will still want you to eventually run the front desk regardless."
            show sc w2cfrontdesk f15
            c"(Drat. I knew I should‚Äôve just worn casual clothes.)"
        "You look great"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc w2cfrontdesk f09
            mc"Nah, I think you look great [c_name]."
            mc"Very professional looking, which is the right attitude to have if you‚Äôre going to potentially run the front desk."
            show sc w2cfrontdesk f12
            $ c_points = change_stat(c_points,2,c_name)
            c"Oh, why thank you [y_name]." #+2 COUSIN POINTS"
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f07
    s"Now let‚Äôs not get ahead of ourselves [y_name]."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f03
    s"My cousin shouldn‚Äôt be pressured into doing this job, it‚Äôs completely up to her."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f01
    s"Before you decide if this kind of job is right for you, there will be some set tasks that I‚Äôm hoping you‚Äôll be able to complete."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f14
    c"Tasks?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f01
    s"Yeah, a variety of tasks, some easier than others, to see if you can handle running the front desk."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f16
    c"Okay, I‚Äôm sure that will be more than fine, I think."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f08
    s"[y_name], after you‚Äôve cleaned up and changed, why don‚Äôt you come and meet me and [c_name] in the reception area."
    s"And when you come back, I‚Äôll go and change as well and quickly take a shower."
    mc"Sounds good. All right, I‚Äôll see you both in a few minutes."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f12
    c"Great!"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (screen goes blank)"
    # (MC has changed now, and heads into the main reception area)"
    scene sc w2cfrontdesk f12
    with dissolve
    mc"(I hope [s_name] goes easy on [c_name].)"
    mc"(We don‚Äôt want her to feel too overawed by this job before she‚Äôs even started it.)"
    mc"(She‚Äôs not quite at the level of confidence that I‚Äôm hoping to get her to yet.)"
    mc"(But working with us today could certainly help matters if she can master the necessary skills that it takes to be the front desk girl of a once popular hotel.)"
    # (MC arrives, where friend and cousin are behind the front counter. S is showing Cousin a few things)"
    # (Friend says to cousin)"
    s"Why don't you take a seat in front of the computer [c_name]?"
    c"Okay."
    # (cousin sits down in front of the laptop)
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f29
    s"So these emails that I‚Äôve highlighted are examples of what I need you to forward to me, as they‚Äôd be regarded as highly important. Got it?"
    c"Yes, I do. This all sounds simple enough."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f18
    s"Excellent. There will be a few days where you‚Äôll have to start very early, like maybe six o‚Äôclock in the morning, but that won‚Äôt be for a few weeks at least."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f19
    s"For now though, you would need to be here by nine o‚Äôclock each morning. Will that be a problem?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f29
    c"No, not at all. Could I have a surf and use one of the showers before I start work?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f18
    s"Yes, of course you can. Just make sure you‚Äôre not smelling of the ocean or seaweed when you start work!"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f30
    c"Haha! I‚Äôll make sure that I don‚Äôt."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f21
    mc"Hey girls. How are you finding things so far [c_name]?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f24
    c"It's not too daunting, so it's been pretty easy so far."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f20
    s"[y_name], you can take over here while I go and get changed."
    mc"What did you want me to show [c_name]?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f21
    s"Nothing in particular, as I‚Äôve pretty much covered the main things I wanted to go through with her on the main computer."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f22
    s"When I get back, we can do some role-playing as guests or clients of the hotel."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f28
    c"Role-playing?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f21
    s"Haha, [y_name] will brief you for what we have in mind. I‚Äôll be back shortly guys."
    # (Friend leaves)"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f36
    mc"So uh, how are you feeling?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f38
    c"I feel pretty good about being here. How have you been since we last spoke?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f37
    mc"I've been pretty good too. Just working hard as usual."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f36
    mc"So what made you want to come by here this morning?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f35
    c"A few reasons. But it was mainly due to my mother‚Äôs influence."
    mc"Your Mom? Trisha made you come here?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f39
    c"She didn‚Äôt make me come here exactly, she just suggested that it would be a great idea for me to build up my confidence and to also help you and [s_name] out."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f37
    c"I‚Äôm studying a hotel management course at college as you know, so I may as well try and put what I‚Äôve learned so far to good use."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f36
    mc"That‚Äôs great to hear [c_name]. But like [s_name] said, there‚Äôs no pressure here."
    mc"Only take the job if you genuinely want it, okay?"
    mc"I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôll know soon enough whether it‚Äôs right for you or not."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f37
    c"Thanks [y_name]."
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f36
    c"So what did [s_name] mean when she said that we‚Äôll be doing some role-playing?"
    mc"Yeah, about that..."
    mc"From what she‚Äôs told me, she and I are going to pretend to be customers or clients who are looking to rent a room for a night or for a few days."
    mc"Or perhaps we may have a complaint about the service that you‚Äôll need to resolve. It could be just about anything."
    mc"But it should be fairly simple. And the two of us will give you pointers on how to manage each situation."
    mc"How does that sound?"
    show sc w2cfrontdesk f37
    c"Well, as long as you guys are going to help me, then I shouldn‚Äôt have anything to worry about."
    mc"Exactly! Anyway, let me show you a few things I‚Äôve learned about the hotel since I first arrived."
    mc"These details might come in handy when you‚Äôre talking with future guests‚Ä¶"
    # (MC stands over cousin, they both look at the PC screen, his hand moving the cursor)"
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (Friend returns)"
    scene sc w2cfrontdesk f53
    with dissolve
    s"All right, are you all set to do some role-playing [c_name]?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f32
    c"Yeah, I think so."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f50
    s"All right, let‚Äôs get to it."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f47
    s"[y_name], come and stand here where I am."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f46
    s"I‚Äôll show [c_name] how to handle bookings and customers who are checking in to the hotel."
    mc"Sure thing [s_name]."
    # (MC stands out front, while friend stands next to cousin behind the counter)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f53
    s"So first of all, we‚Äôre going to pretend that [y_name] is checking into the hotel and that he‚Äôs made a booking online beforehand."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f46
    s"Have you got that [y_name]?"
    mc"Yep, understood."
    s"Okay, so approach the counter [y_name], relaying all the details that I just mentioned."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f51
    s"Watch this very closely [c_name]."
    # (MC approaches the counter)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"Good morning Sir, welcome to the Sunshine Bay Lighthouse Hotel."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f40
    mc"Hi there. I have a reservation under the name, uh, Mister Smith."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"Okay, and do you have a copy of your booking Mister Smith?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f59
    mc"Ahh yes, I have it on my phone."
    # (MC shows friend his phone, pretends to show his booking)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"That‚Äôs fine. Please wait one moment while I check our reservations list..."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f58
    s"Mr. Bob Smith, from Wayward Pines?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f41
    mc"Yes, that would be me."
    # (MC tries not to laugh)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"Thank you Sir. And did you have some identification?"
    mc"Yes, I do."
    # (MC hands friend his driver‚Äôs license)"
    # (Friend turns to cousin)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f61
    s"For guests or customers that don‚Äôt have a copy of their booking, you should be able to look it up in the search bar of the hotel bookings page by using their surname."
    s"Also, the two main forms of identification that we accept are a passport or a driver‚Äôs license."
    s"Make sure that they‚Äôre both current and also check that the photo matches the customer."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f62
    c"Okay, I‚Äôll remember that."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"All right Mister Smith, your booking is through until Sunday morning."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f55
    s"So just to confirm, you‚Äôve booked a single room with a bathtub, and you have requested a view of the ocean."
    s"Is that correct?"
    mc"Yes it is. And my room has a mini-bar included as well, doesn‚Äôt it?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f57
    s"Yes it does."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    s"All of our rooms have mini-bar, cable TV, wi-fi, and the air-conditioning is set to standard room temperature."
    s"I‚Äôll get you to fill out your details on this sheet sir, and we‚Äôll need a deposit from your credit card which will be refunded back to you after you check-out."
    s"It‚Äôs just so we can add any extra expenses to it like from the mini-bar, that is if you decide to purchase anything from there."
    s"If you charge anything else to your room, such as the buffet or anything from the restaurant, or gift shops, then that will be added to your final bill and paid for with your credit card."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f41
    mc"Great. I‚Äôll fill this out now."
    # (Friend turns to cousin)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f61
    s"Always make sure you try and get a major credit card from our guests."
    s"They will know before they make their booking that it is a requirement upon arrival."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f63
    s"Alternatively, if they don‚Äôt have one, then they will be expected to cover any payments before they check out. We can accept cash in this case."
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f56
    mc"All right, done!"
    # (MC hands his sheet)"
    s"Thank you Sir. Your room number is 416."
    s"There are two key cards for your room and you will be expected to return them both upon checking out."
    s"Your check out time is ten a.m, but this can be extended to eleven a.m. or twelve p.m. if required, by request."
    s"If you need anything, day or night, please dial 001 on your hotel room phone and someone will be able to assist you."
    s"The bellboy will take your bags and show you to your room."
    mc"Thank you miss."
    s"Enjoy your stay!"
    # (Friend turns to cousin)"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f61
    s"And that‚Äôs how it‚Äôs done! Any questions?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f63
    c"Uh, do all customer check-ins go as smoothly as that?"
    show  sc w2cfrontdesk f61
