    # ROLLING WIP OF ASHLEY"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j23
    if persistent.v_xray_enabled:
        show screen scr_peeping_tom("sc w2ashleyjogging j23","sc w2ashleyjogging j23x","v_pt_image_index_w2_33")
    mc"(Damn‚Ä¶)"
    hide screen scr_peeping_tom
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j12
    ash"Nice scooter, is it yours?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j07
    mc"No um, I‚Äôm just borrowing it from someone while I‚Äôm staying in Sunshine Bay."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j09
    ash"That‚Äôs nice."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j12
    ash"I have one in my garage that you could‚Äôve had."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j10
    ash"So um, why are you pushing it along rather than riding it?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j07
    mc"Oh‚Ä¶"
    mc"(I better come up with a good lie, and fast. Otherwise, this could be a really embarrassing conversation.)"
    mc"I um, it doesn‚Äôt have any fuel in it."
    mc"I was just pushing it back to the hotel and then I was thinking I could go into town later to get some for it."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j06
    ash"Ahh, okay."
    # (Ashley lifts a leg up and stretches it on the park bench)"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j29
    mc"(Oh man‚Ä¶ She certainly knows how to hold a guy‚Äôs attention.)"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j30
    mc"(Is she doing this on purpose?)"
    mc"(Anyway, I have to ask her what‚Äôs been on my mind since we last spoke.)"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j32
    mc"Ashley, there‚Äôs something I need to ask you."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j07
    mc"Something that I probably should have brought up when we spoke the other day."
    ash"Oh, what did you want to know [y_name]?"
    mc"A lot of things. Like for instance, what happened between you and my father to make you leave?"
    mc"Why did my father never want to talk to me about it after you and [s_name] were gone?"
    mc"And why did you keep [s_name] from being able to contact me?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j08
    ash"You have a lot of questions, which is understandable. And yes, I do owe you an explanation."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j13
    ash"I want you to know that I am truly sorry for that, and for keeping you two apart."
    ash"I have my reasons, but if you give me a chance, then I can tell you everything you need to know."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j08
    ash"Maybe we should take a seat because it‚Äôs going to take some time for me to explain everything to you."
    mc"Okay."
    mc"(Hopefully, she doesn‚Äôt take too long, as I probably should have been back at the hotel by now.)"
    stop ambient fadeout 1.0
    # (screen goes blank)"
    scene black
    with dissolve
    scene black
    with Pause (2)
    # (Ashley and the MC sit down together)"
    scene sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    with dissolve
    play ambient "sound effects/01/01/Birds_in_trees_sounds_effects1.mp3" loop fadeout 1.0 fadein 1.0
    ash"So how are you and [s_name] going with the hotel?"
    mc"We‚Äôre doing pretty well actually."
    mc"We‚Äôre both pretty optimistic about the future, and I feel like we‚Äôre heading in the right direction."
    ash"And are you going to tell her that you ran into me?"
    mc"To be honest,  I‚Äôm not really sure."
    mc"You guys obviously have some issues to deal with, and I don‚Äôt particularly want to be in the middle of that."
    mc"But at the same time, I did promise you the last time we spoke that I would talk to her for you."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j16
    ash"I really would appreciate it if you would [y_name]."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j19
    ash"It hurts that she feels so much resentment towards me."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"However, you shouldn‚Äôt lie to her either."
    ash"I can‚Äôt imagine she would like it if you were to do that to her. I know that full well."
    mc"(Why is Ashley giving me this advice? Is she trying to help, or make things harder for me and [s_name]?)"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    mc"Okay, I‚Äôll tell her that I‚Äôve spoken to you."
    mc"But Ashley, if you want me to talk to [s_name] for you, then I need you to tell me why you and [s_name] moved out."
    mc"I really need to know, because my father has never told me what happened that night."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j19
    ash"(Sigh‚Ä¶)"
    ash"Okay [y_name], I won‚Äôt delay anymore."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"But I must warn you, what I‚Äôm about to say may end up being something you wished you hadn‚Äôt have heard."
    ash"Are you ready to learn the truth about why I left with [s_name] nine years ago and why I kept her from contacting you?"
    mc"Yes, please tell me."
    mc"(I don‚Äôt care what it is, or if it pisses me off, I just want the truth.)"
    ash"All right, but you have to keep this between us."
    mc"Of course, I promise."
    ash"Okay..."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    ash"Well, a few weeks before I moved out of you and your father‚Äôs home with [s_name]..."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"You may have noticed that your Dad and I had been arguing quite a lot."
    mc"Yes, I do remember."
    mc"At first I thought you two would get over it, but then your fights seemed to worsen by the day."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    ash"Did you ever listen in on what we were fighting about?"
    mc"No, I just tried to block it out. My room wasn‚Äôt as close to you and Dad‚Äôs as [s_name]‚Äôs was."
    mc"So she probably heard a lot more than I did."
    mc"But I remember the night before you both left, you and my Dad had the worst of all of your fights. It was certainly the most vocal."
    mc"Even with my headphones on, I could still hear both of you arguing and shouting at each other."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j21
    ash"I‚Äôm really sorry that you had to hear that [y_name], and that it‚Äôs still fresh in your mind."
    # (Ashley‚Äôs eyes drop down, unsure how to say the next bit)"
    ash"Oh boy, how do I say this."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"[y_name], I want you to know that I loved your father very much."
    ash"The fact that I was willing to move in with him and give up everything I had here I hope proves that to you."
    ash"And the first few years that [s_name] and I lived with him, with you, and even with Rosa, it was amazing."
    ash"I thought I was living in a fairytale at times."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j21
    ash"But not all fairytales have happy endings, and my relationship with your father was no exception."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    mc"He did something to you, didn‚Äôt he Ashley?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"As I may have mentioned to you before, your father was never violent with me."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    ash"In the end, he wanted something else. He just could never admit that to me or himself."
    mc"Something else? What else could he possibly want?"
    ash"Another woman I guess."
    # (screen shakes)"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    with vpunch
    mc"Oh my god!? My Dad was cheating on you?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j21
    ash"I‚Äôm afraid so [y_name]. I was hoping you would never find out."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    mc"No, it can‚Äôt be true. My Dad would never do that. Would he?"
    ash"It‚Äôs true [y_name]."
    ash"I know you want to believe your Dad wouldn‚Äôt do such a thing, especially after losing your mother, but I caught him red-handed."
    mc"How though? What proof did you have?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j19
    ash"Well, when our arguments first began, I wasn‚Äôt one hundred percent sure if your father was being unfaithful."
    ash"At first, I thought I was just being paranoid."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    ash"But while you were at school, and your father was home from sea, there used to be random phone calls made to the house during the day."
    ash"Whenever I‚Äôd answer the phone, there‚Äôd be no-one on the other end or they‚Äôd hang up."
    ash"But whenever your father answered, he always had a conversation with someone on the other end of the line."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"I‚Äôd ask him who it was, and he would nonchalantly tell me it was one of his navy buddies."
    mc"Phone calls don‚Äôt prove anything Ashley."
    ash"No they don‚Äôt, but a pair of ladies underwear in the back seat of our car, panties that definitely weren‚Äôt mine, certainly does."
    mc"Oh, are you serious??"
    ash"Deadly‚Ä¶ I initially didn‚Äôt say anything, because I still needed some hard proof."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    ash"After what I discovered in the car, it took me a few weeks to find anything that would incriminate your father."
    ash"What I discovered were messages exchanged with your Dad and some mystery woman online."
    ash"And I also found out that he was returning home from shore a few days earlier than he had told us..."
    ash"Just so he could spend that extra time with this woman that he was cheating on me with."
    mc"How do you know this?"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j15
    ash"It was in one of his messages that he exchanged with this woman."
    ash"He told her that he was coming home early, and she asked him to meet her at the ‚Äúusual place‚Äù."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"I never found out where this place was though."
    mc"Okay. But did you ever find out who the woman he was allegedly seeing was?"
    ash"No, I never found out, and he never told me."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j21
    ash"Her username for their chats was something like claret, twenty, ten, or twenty eleven. I can‚Äôt remember exactly."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"Her real name was never mentioned in any of the chats that I had read between them."
    ash"Anyway, the very last fight that I had with your father, I demanded that he tell me who she was, or I would threaten to move out and take [s_name] with me."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    ash"He refused to tell me, so I was left with no other choice."
    ash"I barely got any sleep that night, and while I lay there in the bed that I shared with him, staring at the ceiling,"
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j14
    ash"I made a decision to move out and to return here to Sunshine Bay with [s_name]."
    ash"I didn‚Äôt think at the time just how much all of this would affect you or my daughter."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j24
    ash"All I knew was that I couldn‚Äôt take any more of your father‚Äôs lies or deceitful ways."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j19
    # (MC looks down at the floor, a stunned look on his face)"
    mc"I can‚Äôt believe this. I can‚Äôt believe my Dad would do this to you."
    ash"I‚Äôm so sorry you had to find out like this [y_name]."
    show sc w2ashleyjogging j21
    ash"But I hope you now understand why I kept you and [s_name] from being able to contact each other."
    jump lb_w2_mow_mc_ashley_1

label lb_w2_mow_mc_ashley_1:
