label lb_w2_vic_date_menu:
    # [The restaurant / The hotel / The future]"

    if v_w2_vicdate_restaurant and v_w2_vicdate_hotel and v_w2_vicdate_future:
        jump lb_w2_vic_date_ending
    menu:
        "The restaurant" if v_w2_vicdate_restaurant == False:
            $ v_w2_vicdate_restaurant = True
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            vic"Now that you‚Äôre here, what are your first impressions of this place?"
            mc"I definitely like the setup that they have. It‚Äôs unlike anything I‚Äôve ever seen before."
            mc"We don‚Äôt have restaurants like this back home, mainly just clubs, pubs, and more intimate restaurants or cafes."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            vic"I‚Äôve been told that the guys who run this place like to change the theme and setting for the show once every six months, just to keep things fresh."
            show sc w2vicdate v23
            vic"So later in the year, the stage show will be something completely different, as will the three-course dinner options."
            show sc w2vicdate v24
            vic"Even the cast that performs on stage will change and some new faces will become a part of the entertainment."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            mc"That‚Äôs interesting."
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            mc"A medieval theme or a history or rock‚Äôn‚Äôroll show I think would work well in a place like this."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            vic"Yeah, I could see that working."
            show sc w2vicdate v23
            jump lb_w2_vic_date_menu


        "The hotel" if v_w2_vicdate_hotel == False:
            $ v_w2_vicdate_hotel = True
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            vic"So you‚Äôve been in town for almost a week now."
            vic"Does it feel like home yet or is to too early to say?"
            mc"Haha, definitely a little early for that kind of talk."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            mc"At the moment it still feels like I‚Äôm on holiday, even despite the amount of work I‚Äôve been doing with [s_name] on the hotel."
            mc"I‚Äôve enjoyed being here for the most part though."
            show sc w2vicdate v20
            vic"That‚Äôs great to hear."
            show sc w2vicdate v22
            vic"And what about [s_name]‚Äôs hotel?"
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            vic"How confident are you of bringing it back to its former glory days?"
            mc"At the moment, if you don‚Äôt mind me using a courtroom saying‚Ä¶"
            mc"The jury‚Äôs still out on that one Vicky."
            mc"But early signs look good. We‚Äôre close to recruiting some important people that we both agree will be hugely beneficial to the success of [s_name]'s hotel."
            mc"It would be even better to have you on-board in a more influential role though, as me and [s_name] both see you as an important part of what we‚Äôre trying to achieve."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            vic"It‚Äôs nice to be thought of like that."
            show sc w2vicdate v21
            vic"As you know, [s_name] and I have been friends for several years now, and as much as I‚Äôd love to help her, time is a major issue for me at the moment."
            show sc w2vicdate v18
            mc"I understand."
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            mc"Your food truck business is very important to you, and splitting your time between that and helping us is probably not as easy as it seems, right?"
            vic"No it isn‚Äôt, but I‚Äôm sure we can figure something out."
            show sc w2vicdate v22
            jump lb_w2_vic_date_menu

        "The future" if v_w2_vicdate_future == False:
            $  v_w2_vicdate_future = True
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            vic"So what are your plans for the future?"
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            vic"Do you think you might have a career in the hotel industry?"
            mc"Haha, it‚Äôs highly unlikely."
            show sc w2vicdate v17
            mc"There‚Äôs so much work that goes into running a hotel than I first realised, and you‚Äôre more reliant on other people rather than just yourself."
            show sc w2vicdate v22
            mc"But who knows? By the end of the summer, my tune may have changed entirely."
            show sc w2vicdate v23
            vic"I think once you see the possibilities, and what you can do with [s_name]‚Äôs hotel when you start getting guests staying there..."
            show sc w2vicdate v19
            vic"I‚Äôm certain that it will give you a completely different perspective compared to what you‚Äôve seen so far."
            show sc w2vicdate v22
            jump lb_w2_vic_date_menu




